22	## Runtime Architecture
23	
24	The runtime is a pipeline.  Each stage is a separate file under `runtime/src/`:
25	
26	```
27	source text
28	  \u{2192} normalizer.py        Unicode symbols \u{2192} __TOKEN__ keywords
29	  \u{2192} grammar.lark         Lark Earley parser
30	  \u{2192} transformer.py       Lark tree \u{2192} AST (ast.py nodes)
31	  \u{2192} sorts.py             SortRegistry: maps type names to Z3 sorts
32	  \u{2192} instantiate.py       Creates Z3 constants for schema variables;
33	                         expands sub-schema fields (task.duration, \u{2026})
34	  \u{2192} translate.py         AST expressions/constraints \u{2192} Z3 expressions
35	  \u{2192} evaluate.py          EvidentSolver: runs the Z3 Solver, extracts model
36	  \u{2192} runtime.py           EvidentRuntime: top-level API (load_source, query)
37	```
38	
39	Supporting modules:
40	- `env.py` \u{2014} immutable variable environment (name \u{2192} Z3 expr)
41	- `quantifiers.py` \u{2014} \u{2200} / \u{2203} constraint translation
42	- `compose.py` \u{2014} names-match schema composition
43	- `evidence.py` \u{2014} derivation trees returned from queries
44	- `sets.py` \u{2014} set/array constraint translation
45	- `sorts.py` \u{2014} Z3 sort registry; also owns enum variant name \u{2192} constructor map
46	- `fixedpoint.py` \u{2014} forward implication rules (A, B \u{21d2} C) via Z3 Fixedpoint
47	- `ast_types.py` \u{2014} re-exports parser AST so runtime shares the same class objects
48	  (critical: isinstance checks break if two separate module instances exist)
